# Persistent Memory (agent-memory)

This project uses [agent-memory](https://github.com/jeffvestal/agent-memory) —
Elasticsearch as persistent semantic memory for Claude Code agents.

## When to Use Memory

| Need | Command |
|---|---|
| Recall context from prior sessions | `bridge recall "<what you're looking for>"` |
| Search indexed project files | `bridge entity search "<query>"` |
| Store a decision or observation | `bridge remember "<text>" [--type feedback\|project\|reference]` |
| Check session history | `bridge history` |
| See current memory status | `bridge status` |

**Decision routing:**
- Use `bridge recall` for memories you or prior sessions explicitly stored (decisions, preferences, observations)
- Use `bridge entity search` for content from project files indexed from BRIDGE_WATCH_DIRS
- Use `bridge status` to confirm ES is online before relying on memory

## Automatic Behaviors (via hooks)

- **Session start**: Syncs memory files from `~/.claude/projects/.../memory/` to ES
- **File writes**: Indexes `.md` files to the entity search index automatically
- **Session end**: Logs session summary to `agent-sessions` index

## Configuration

Memory is stored in Elasticsearch. The following must be set in `.env` (in the agent-memory directory):

```
BRIDGE_ES_URL=https://...elastic.cloud
BRIDGE_ES_API_KEY=<scoped key>
BRIDGE_AGENT_ID=<your agent name>
BRIDGE_WATCH_DIRS=/path/to/dirs/to/index
BRIDGE_MEMORY_PATH=/path/to/claude/memory/dir
```
